## 3. Solution Overview

### High-Level Architecture Summary
Describe the overall architecture style.

Default guidance:
- For most MVPs, prefer a well-structured **modular monolith** or a small number of coarse-grained services.
- Defer a fine-grained microservices architecture until there are clear, project-specific reasons.

### Recommended Architecture Style
Select one, and justify clearly:
- modular monolith (default choice for MVP)
- monolith + separate AI orchestration worker
- small set of coarse-grained services
- microservices (only if strongly justified)
- serverless
- event-driven
- hybrid

### Architecture Rationale
Explain why this architecture style was chosen for this specific project.

Guidance:
- If you choose microservices, explain why a modular monolith is insufficient **for this AI product** (team size, scaling characteristics, regulatory separation, etc.) and call out the operational overhead.
- If you choose a modular monolith, describe how you will keep clear module boundaries so future extraction is possible if needed.

### Design Alternatives and Trade-offs
Briefly describe at least one simpler alternative and why you did not choose it, and any risks of over-engineering or under-engineering.

