## 4. Application Architecture

### Functional Modules / Components
List the major application components.

### Responsibilities of Each Module

#### Authentication Module
Responsibilities:
- user registration
- login
- token issuance
- password reset

#### Workout Module
Responsibilities:
- create workout entries
- store workout sessions
- retrieve workout history

#### Booking Module
Responsibilities:
- reserve class slots
- cancel bookings
- enforce booking rules

### Application Interaction Flow
Describe how components interact.

### Component Diagram (required)
Add a mermaid diagram showing the main runtime components (UI, gateway/API, backend services/modules, AI orchestrator, databases, caches, external APIs).

```mermaid
graph TD;
    UI[User Interface] --> API[API Gateway / Backend];
    API --> S1[Service / Module 1];
    API --> S2[Service / Module 2];
    S1 --> DB[(Primary Database)];
    S2 --> Cache[(Cache)];
    API --> AI[AI Orchestrator / LLM];
    API --> EXT[External APIs];
```

### Key Business Flows
Document major flows.

#### Flow 1: User logs workout
1. User submits workout details from app
2. API validates request
3. Workout module stores session
4. Response returned to client

#### Flow 2: User books class
1. User selects class
2. Booking module checks membership status
3. Booking module checks class capacity
4. Booking stored
5. Confirmation returned

### Sequence Diagram Placeholder
Describe sequence flow in text or reference separate diagram.

